Define Functions In JS

Functions are ways to declare something that you want or perform certain tasks !
or 

In JavaScript, functions are likened to recipes in a cookbook,
guiding the computer on tasks, such as adding numbers or altering webpage colors, serving to organize code,
prevent redundancy, and enable the reuse of specific instructions, thereby enhancing code clarity and structure.

function myFunction(p1, p2) {
  return p1 * p2;
}
